comment_regular_data.body:
[![CLA assistant check](https://cla-assistant.io/pull/badge/not_signed)](https://cla-assistant.io/TokTok/hs-toxcore?pullRequest=120)
Thank you for your submission, we really appreciate it. Like many open source projects, we ask that you sign our [Contributor License Agreement](https://cla-assistant.io/TokTok/hs-toxcore?pullRequest=120) before we can accept your contribution.
Could you clarify what is meant in the CLA by a license "approved by" the FSF? Could this include permissive licenses like MIT? If so, do you actually plan to release the code under such a license?

We want to release the software under an as-free-as-possible license. In the case of hstox, it's AGPLv3. This clause allows us to make exceptions for specific use cases such as iOS apps. In the case of hstox, it's unlikely we'll be releasing it on iOS. The specific exception we need to make to permit such a release would be constructed by a lawyer in order to preserve as many of the AGPL requirements as possible.
Can't say I like the sound of that. But you plan to get explicit FSF approval for your custom license?

Nevermind. Having looked some more into the tivoisation practices of iOS, which appear to be clearly incompatible with the spirit as well as the letter of the GPLv3 and with software freedom in general, I'm afraid I can't sign the agreement. A pity.

I don't actually want to obstruct fixing these bugs though... so I hereby give the TokTok project permission to make use of the code submitted in this pull request for whatever purposes they see fit, including incorporating it into the hs-toxcore project and releasing it under arbitrary licenses and conditions.
